@jgoppert With the latest (https://github.com/PX4/Firmware/commit/66b9ee2d24c0c91900fb270f4996305d8bac9b13) changes of LPE (fusion mask, etc), I have some serious issues. Z estimation does not take LIDAR measurements into account. LIDAR sometimes is reported as ok, but mostly faults with no (at least reported) recovery. Raw lidar measurements however are ok without any dropouts. 
I have set the fusion mask to 148 in order to disable AGL, GPS, vision Yaw and Flow as I purely rely on vision position estimates. LPE_VIS_Z and LPE_BARO I have set to maximum (to rely on LIDAR only). 
As a result, I get a Z estimation that seems to rely on the accelerator measurements only.

I've been testing the camera trigger and haven't got it working on Pins 5&6 of the FMU (TRIG_PINS = 56). I've also tried the setting TRIG_PINS = 34 which works fine.
I'm wondering if there was a bug introduced somewhere because the default pins are in fact 5,6.
@birchera Do you guys have the same issue?

These lines crash the nsh_script execution if a variable is referenced in your script that doesn't exist.  Notice there is no NULL check on the var_value.  This is inside nsh_parse.

char *var_value = getenv(var_name_start);
*var_name_end = tmp_char;
res_size += strlen(var_value);

How do you go about fixing Nuttx bugs ?

@LorenzMeier why are we using `MAV_CMD_PREFLIGHT_REBOOT_SHUTDOWN` with `param1 == 3` as link shutdown? https://github.com/PX4/Firmware/blob/7d7e40f59473ed538c61f8b76020ca505ee52487/src/modules/mavlink/mavlink_receiver.cpp#L353

According to the specs that should do an FC reboot with forcing it to bootloader. Which is implemented but never happens because of the above logic.

Funnily this could have been the same issue: https://github.com/PX4/Firmware/pull/5473 (although normal boot was ok for him I guess)

