It pre-filters accel and gyro data before it's used in the attitude_estimator_q.

@bkueng please have a look through, thanks.

Noticed this problem when flying the Solo in SITL. For some reason the mag field states (earth field and bias) are not correctly learned in the drone will eventually loose heading and start toilet bowling.
Forcing the filter to use the simpler heading fusion (EKF2_MAG_TYPE=1)  eliminates the problem.
@CarlOlsson Maybe this could be related to your replay problems. Can you confirm that 3D mag fusion is working on real hardware?
